  "body": "## Description\nFollowing the Merge, Besu needs a new sync strategy that takes advantage of POS mechanics and can get users up and validating faster. Besu also needs to address lingering issues with sync that makes it slow or freeze. \n\n### Goals:\n* New sync strategy based around backwards sync\n  * Backwards syncing in all cases in a performant, useful manner \n  * Download blockchain in the background  \n    * Use 8 seconds of free slot time for background download\n  * Better post-Merge sync target based on the CL blocks and what we receive from the CL\n  * If we have deposit logs (Teku), immediately start validating when worldstate download is complete \n  * Consider implications for private networks (leave fast unchanged, update snap)\n  * Decide on sync modes:\n    * Backward snap ?\n    * Backward checkpoint ?\n    * Backward validator sync (no blockchain) ? \n    * Full sync strategy\n    * auto-detect lock-step sync with CL, switch to optimistic head rather than relying on fcU\n* Peering for improving sync performance\n  * When receiving an empty response, retry logic polls new peers #5271\n  * Flag peer as useless/demoted \n* Storage enhancements to limit IO and disk usage #5387\n  * Blob DB #4607 (?)\n* Sync resiliency\n  * Detecting if sync is stalled and restart the sync (or a portion) \n \n### Reminders\n* Update [dappnode packages](https://github.com/dappnode?q=besu&type=all&language=&sort=) ",
